t for Oscars' Best International Film |work=The New York Times |accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nA 16-year-old girl and a middle-aged doctor connect in Budapest after World War II, each mourning their families lost in concentration camps.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[K\u00e1roly Hajduk]] as K\u00f6rner Alad\u00e1r\n* [[Abig\u00e9l Sz\u00f5ke]] as Wiener Kl\u00e1ra\n* [[Mari Nagy]] as Olgi\n* [[Barnab\u00e1s Horkay]] as Pepe\n* [[Katalin Simk\u00f3]] as Erzsi\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Hungarian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|9081558|Those Who Remained}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Those Who Remained}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 drama films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian drama films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian-language films]]\n[[Category:Holocaust films]]\n{{Hungary-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Those Who Remained\n| image          = Those Who Remained.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Barnab\u00e1s T\u00f3th (director)|Barnab\u00e1s T\u00f3th]]\n| producer       = M\u00f3nika M\u00e9cs\n| writer         = Barnab\u00e1s T\u00f3th<br>Kl\u00e1ra Muhi\n| starring       = [[K\u00e1roly Hajduk]]<br>[[Abig\u00e9l Sz\u00f5ke]]\n| music          = L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Pirisi\n| cinematography = G\u00e1bor Marosi\n| editing        = \u00c1gnes M\u00f3gor\n| distributor    = Budapest Film\n| released       = {{film date|2019|8|30|[[Telluride Film Festival|Telluride FF]]|2019|9|26|Hungary|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 83 minutes\n| country        = Hungary\n| language       = Hungarian\n| budget         = \n| gross          = $119,599<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |title=Those Who Remained|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&wk=2019W39&id=_fTHOSEWHOREMAINED01 |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=26 November 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Those Who Remained''''' ({{lang-hu|'''Akik maradtak'''}}) is a 2019 Hungarian [[drama film]] directed by [[Barnab\u00e1s T\u00f3th (director)|Barnab\u00e1s T\u00f3th]]. It was selected as the Hungarian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Best International Feature Film]] at the [[92nd Academy Awards]],<ref name=\"Hungary\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/awards/oscars-academy-awards-telluride-those-who-remained-1203321295/ |title=Post-Holocaust Drama ''Those Who Remained'' Is Hungary's Oscar Entry |last=Barraclough |first=Leo |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=3 September 2019 |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref> making the December shortlist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2019/12/16/us/ap-us-oscars-international-film-shortlist.html |title=10 Films Make Shortlist for Oscars' Best International Film |work=The New York Times |accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nA 16-year-old girl and a middle-aged doctor connect in Budapest after World War II, each mourning their families lost in concentration camps.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[K\u00e1roly Hajduk]] as K\u00f6rner Alad\u00e1r\n* [[Abig\u00e9l Sz\u00f5ke]] as Wiener Kl\u00e1ra\n* [[Mari Nagy]] as Olgi\n* [[Barnab\u00e1s Horkay]] as Pepe\n* [[Katalin Simk\u00f3]] as Erzsi\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Hungarian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|9081558|Those Who Remained}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Those Who Remained}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2019 drama films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian drama films]]\n[[Category:Hungarian-language films]]\n[[Category:Holocaust films]]\n{{Hungary-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Those_Who_Remained"}
{"title_page": "Bob Dylan bibliography", "text_new": "{{short description|List of books published by and about Bob Dylan}}\nThis is a list of books published by and about [[Bob Dylan]].\n\n==Books by Bob Dylan==\n\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=[[Tarantula (Dylan book)|Tarantula]]|publisher=[[Macmillan Publishers (United States)|Macmillan]]|year=1971|isbn=0261633376}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=[[Writings and Drawings by Bob Dylan]]|publisher=[[Jonathan Cape]]|year=1973|isbn=0-224-00867-6}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=Lyrics: 1962\u20131985|publisher=[[Alfred A. Knopf|Knopf]]|year=1985|isbn=978-0394542782}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=[[Chronicles: Volume One]]|publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]] |year=2004|isbn=0-7432-2815-4}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=Lyrics: 1962\u20132001|publisher=Simon & Schuster |year=2004|isbn=0-7432-3944X}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=The Lyrics: Since 1962|publisher=Simon & Schuster |year=2014|isbn=978-1476797700}} Edited by [[Christopher Ricks]], Lisa Nemrow, Julie Nemrow.<ref>{{cite news| url = http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/07/the-most-of-bob-dylan/| title = The Most of Bob Dylan| author = Kozinn, Alann| date = October 7, 2014| accessdate = October 8, 2014| publisher = New York Times}}</ref>\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=The Nobel Lecture|publisher=Simon & Schuster |year=2017|isbn=978-1501189401}}\n\n==Art books by Bob Dylan==\n\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title=Drawn Blank |publisher= [[Random House]]|year=1994|isbn= 978-0679417880}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title= The Drawn Blank Series |publisher=[[Prestel Publishing|Prestel]]|year=2008 |isbn= 978-3791339436}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title= The Brazil Series |publisher=Prestel| year=2010|isbn= 978-3791350981}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last=Dylan|title= The Asia Series |publisher= [[Gagosian Gallery]] \n|year=2011|isbn= 978-1935263470}}\n*{{Cite book|first=Bob|last